<item>
            <title>[LU-17366] kernel update [SLES15 SP5 5.14.21-150500.55.39.1]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17366</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SUSE Linux Enterprise 15 SP5 kernel was updated to receive various security&lt;br/&gt;
and bugfixes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following security bugs were fixed:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-6176: Fixed a denial of service in the cryptographic algorithm&lt;br/&gt;
    scatterwalk functionality (bsc#1217332).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-2006: Fixed a race condition in the RxRPC network protocol&lt;br/&gt;
    (bsc#1210447).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-5633: Fixed a use-after-free flaw in the way memory objects were&lt;br/&gt;
    handled when they were being used to store a surface (bsc#1216527).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-39197: Fixed a out-of-bounds read in nf_conntrack_dccp_packet()&lt;br/&gt;
    (bsc#1216976).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-4244: Fixed a use-after-free in the nf_tables component, which&lt;br/&gt;
    could be exploited to achieve local privilege escalation (bsc#1215420).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-6039: Fixed a use-after-free in lan78xx_disconnect in&lt;br/&gt;
    drivers/net/usb/lan78xx.c (bsc#1217068).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-45863: Fixed a out-of-bounds write in fill_kobj_path()&lt;br/&gt;
    (bsc#1216058).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-5158: Fixed a denial of service in vringh_kiov_advance() in&lt;br/&gt;
    drivers/vhost/vringh.c in the host side of a virtio ring (bsc#1215710).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-45871: Fixed an issue in the IGB driver, where the buffer size may&lt;br/&gt;
    not be adequate for frames larger than the MTU (bsc#1216259).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-5717: Fixed a heap out-of-bounds write vulnerability in the&lt;br/&gt;
    Performance Events component (bsc#1216584).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-39198: Fixed a race condition leading to use-after-free in&lt;br/&gt;
    qxl_mode_dumb_create() (bsc#1216965).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-25775: Fixed improper access control in the Intel Ethernet&lt;br/&gt;
    Controller RDMA driver (bsc#1216959).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CVE-2023-46862: Fixed a NULL pointer dereference in io_uring_show_fdinfo()&lt;br/&gt;
    (bsc#1216693).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The following non-security bugs were fixed:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.suse.com/pipermail/sle-security-updates/2023-December/017384.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.suse.com/pipermail/sle-security-updates/2023-December/017384.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
